        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Well this is what I am doing at 55 buds.</P><P>I am using a combo of root dot and fear as I can not seems to get the root to be safe enough for me.  I am deeply concerned about getting killed here as I will never get a cleric to come in and rez me.</P><P>Here is what I am currently doing:</P><P>Jacker - Fear Kiting him.<BR>I am sitting my pet down at the base of his building and casting Cascade on him, then sending pet in.  I cast fear on him, Splurt, and BOD to recover the HT hp loss.</P><P>That is enough to outdamage the pet.  Now he will fear path up the ramp towards the exit to Nek forest.  I run up and move to the ledge across from the ramp where he will path back and forth.</P><P>When his Fear Drops I refear, if his dark drops first I run to the top of the ramp and wait for him to come up to me.  That gives me  enough time to cast fear without getting hit.</P><P>At the end of the fight I have 80 mana and full hps.</P><P>Ok Next one is Mrak, I park pet at base of Jackers house again and pull with Cascade, when he comes out of building I root him and apply splurt and IB.  I then switch out Root for Fear and wait for root to break when it does I send in pet and Fear him, he will go up the ramp and path badly again, I run up ramp and cast dark on him again then sit on ledge and reapply Splurt and IB and one BOD.</P><P>That leaves me with 60 mana and full hps at the end.</P><P>Same thing for the last one warrior.</P><P>Now I can get all three within one cycle and be ready for Jacker again with good mana and hp.  I do not try the fourth one yet as my mana is a bit low and I do not want to risk it. </P><P>Ok I changed to Rooting first as I could not get enough damage on the mob before my pet killed them.  Hence I wait for the first wave of DOTs to dig in deep before sending the pet in.</P><P>Also I decided that I would not get killed here and thus decided to keep him in the ramp feared as it allows for easy pathing to run from the ledge to the top of the ramp with DMF and get that cast of fear off even if the  darkness fails.  I have only died here due to a lag and LD and would be surprised if you did otherwise.  </P><P>Beaware that running into the Arena to be killed is Bannable, and running to the zone is easy and very safe.  Also from my experiences Jacker has not yet joined in the fight if I pull past him along the ramp going to the zone line.</P><P>That is how I am doing it, I do a full cycle and then do things around the house some time which is why I love this.  Previous posts have better mana efficent ways but I have found this to be the safest way to do it with the intention of taking a break every couple cycles to do something else and medding up to full.</P><P>Love this camp and will stay here till 56 for sure then go find another zone to play in.</P><P>Hope that helps.</P><P>Dian Cryptmaker<BR>Lvl 54 Deathgiver<BR>On Terris-Thule<BR>Of the Clan Battle Cry</font></td>
